Cambodian King pays tribute to President Kim Il Sung
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk and his party visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on  Tuesday to pay tribute to the President Kim Il Sung.
Accompanying the guests were President Kim Yong Nam of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun and  DPRK ambassador to Cambodia Kim Yong Sop.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Flags of the  Worker's Party of Korea and the DPRK and  standards of the Korean People's Army were standing by both sides of the statue of the President.
   A guard of honor of the three services of the KPA lined up there.
   A floral basket in the name of the Cambodian King was laid before the statue of the President.   Written on the ribbon hanging from the basket were letters "highest tribute to H.E. Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, President of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After expressing humble reverence before the President's statue, the King entered the hall where the President lies in state and made a bow to him in the most profound reverence.   The King looked round with keen interest the orders and medals awarded to the President by foreign countries, the train used by him for his on-site guidance and foreign trip, and the  car he used in the last days of his life.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The King wrote in the visitor's book that  Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, President of the DPRK, is the eternal sun of humankind, the vanguard fighter who waged a struggle against imperialism and colonialism and for progress and the great man who enjoyed high authority and prestige on the international arena.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Great successes were made  in the struggle for socialism and communism in this land where the Korean nation lives thanks to his brilliant wisdom and leadership, he said, and added:   The Cambodian people will make positive efforts to achieve peace, progress and prosperity following the noble examples shown by him in the struggle for the national independence and the prosperity of the country.

Banquet given for Cambodian King
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- The presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK gave a banquet at the Mansudae assembly hall today in honor of H.M. Norodom Sihanouk, King of Cambodia, on an official goodwill visit to Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present on invitation were H.M. Queen, deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace of Cambodia Kong Sam Ol, Minister of State of the Royal Government and Concurrently Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation of Cambodia Hor Namhong, Cambodian Ambassador E.P. to Korea Oum Mannorine and those accompanying the King.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present there were President Kim Yong Nam of the presidium of the SPA of the DPRK, Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun and personages concerned.Kim Yong Nam, addressing the banquet, said the current Korea visit of esteemed H.M. King Norodom Sihanouk stemmed from the noble sense of moral obligation to express his wholehearted respects to the great President Kim Il Sung who is preserved in state and share pains of the loss with the Korean people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his lifetime President Kim Il Sung, he noted,  set great store by the intimacy with esteemed H.M. King and always respected and supported H.M. King's independent stand on the Cambodian issue in either good time or hard time. 
Kim Il Sung gave material aid and moral support to the patriotic cause of the King until the last period of his great life, Kim Yong Nam said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Yong Nam said esteemed H.M. King spoke highly of Kim Il Sung as an outstanding thinker and theoretician, a distinguished hero and the sun of humankind. 
   He said:   You established unbreakable relations of friendship with Kim Il Sung and received incalculable kindness from Kim Il Sung. You have regarded this as the greatest fortune and worked all along  to discharge your obligation and duty as befits a real brother and a close comrade-in-arms.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Whenever the opportunity presented itself, you expressed infinite respect and reverence for Kim Il Sung and the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il and supported the efforts of the Korean people to pull through difficulties, Kim Yong Nam said, expressing deep thanks for this.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He highly praised H.M. King for having devotedly worked for terminating a civil war and paving the path of the nation as the father of the Khmer nation for a long time as well as for conducting energetic activities for unity and cohesion of the nation and territorial integrity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people treasure the amity with the Cambodian people that President Kim Il Sung worked together with H.M. 
King to provide and develop in his lifetime and will make every possible effort to expand and develop it in different fields, Kim Yong Nam added.
   H.M. King Norodom Sihanouk spoke next at the banquet.

Speech of King Norodom Sihanouk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk, King of Cambodia, made a speech at the banquet given in his honor by the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today.He said among other things:   My dearest and most fervent wish and that of queen Norodom Monineath Sihanouk these years have always been to visit Korea again to express our most profound respect, our veneration, our infinite gratitude and our boundless admiration to his excellency Generalissimo Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His excellency Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, President of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, is the sun of progressive, anti-colonialist and anti-imperialist humanity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He and his most dignified and illustrious successor, his excellency Marshal Kim Jong Il, supreme leader of the Korean nation and people, enjoy highest international prestige. They are not only geniuses of Korea, a paradise of Juche of multiple and grand realizations, most developed in all domains of socialist and communist construction and national edification, but also a symbol of purest and most heroic patriotism and firm solidarity with all the peoples who fight for national liberation, complete independence of the motherland and triumph of the ideas of justice, peace and progress.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   That is why during our struggles for national liberation, the Cambodian people and I received benefits of most powerful and fraternal support and many-sided and very generous aid from his excellency Generalissimo Kim Il Sung and his excellency Marshal Kim Jong Il, supreme leader of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   My family, my followers and myself will never forget the benefits that the two great leaders venerated and loved by the valiant Korean people gave us most generously during the darkest period in our life and our contemporary history.   We will cherish very profound and eternal gratitude to the two leaders and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On behalf of the Kingdom of Cambodia and my own behalf, I extend our warmest felicitations and admiration to his excellency Marshal Kim Jong Il, supreme leader of the glorious Democratic People's Republic of Korea, for the great realizations in his historic cause of socialist and communist construction and national edification and express our total and full support for the most patriotic and most just proposals formulated by his excellency Generalissimo-President Kim Il Sung and his most illustrious successor for the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In that sentiment, the Cambodian King proposed a toast to the incomparable and immortal glory of his excellency Generalissimo-President Kim Il Sung, to the good health, long life, happiness and glory of his excellency Marshal Kim Jong Il, supreme leader, and to the indestructible friendship between the Kingdom of Cambodia and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.

Kumsusan Memorial Palace, sacred ground of revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- An increasing number of people visit the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to commemorate the 5th death anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung (July 8).   The time-honored palace is where the President conducted energetic activities for the Korean and the world revolution while leading the affairs of the  Worker's Party of Korea and the state. Korea made efforts to build the Kumsusan assembly hall into the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to open it to the public on the occasion of  death anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to the infinite loyalty and filial piety of General Secretary Kim Jong Il to the late leader that the palace stands as the sacred temple.   He gave instructions about colors and patterns of marble and even a tree to be planted in an arboretum around the palace, to say nothing of the examination of the layout table of the palace.  Numerous was his visit to the construction site to solve knotty problems.   The palace is excellent in content, shape, size and detailed decoration.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Standing in the hall against the backdrop of blue sky and red glow on the first floor is the statue of the President.    After mounting the grand staircase of more than one hundred stairs, 18 metres wide, through the hall you arrive at the spacious hall the floor and walls of which are red marble. Preserved there in state is the President. The visitors pay their deepest respects to  the President and harden their determinations to remain loyal to Kim Jong Il, true to the behest of the President.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Preserved with much care in the palace are a car used by the President in the last days of his life and a passenger train used by him during his foreign trip and for his on-site guidance, as well as orders and medals awarded to him by many countries around the world.   In front of the palace is a plaza covering 100,000 square metres and around the palace is the arboretum of one million square metres in which hundreds of species of flowers and trees grow.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The palace has nearly 1,000 metre long access corridor, tram cars running on the track of several kilometers and other facilities arranged for the convenience of the people who visit the palace under rough weather conditions.

Reception for  organizations for study of Juche idea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- A reception was given in Pyongyang yesterday for delegations and delegate of organizations for the study of the Juche idea, on a visit to Korea on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Invited there were director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea Shuhachi Inoue, chairman of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli and his party, the delegation of the Sri Lanka Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, the Jordanian delegation for the Study of the Juche Idea and the delegate of the Ethiopian Organization for the Study of the Juche Idea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Yang Hyong Sop, vice-President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, made an address there.   He said that the President's great exploits performed for the fatherland, people, era and history would shine forever with the century.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    He noted that the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il successfully realized the cause of upholding the eternal leader at the highest level and is constantly strengthening and developing the socialist country of Juche into a powerful country.   He wished the delegates of organizations for the study of the Juche idea greater successes in the work for studying and disseminating the Juche idea, increasing the ranks of followers of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea said that the President was the greatest of great men who founded the great revolutionary idea and method of leadership and devoted his whole life to the people, taking it as the maxim "to believe in people as in heaven."   Noting that the President is the eternal leader not only of the Korean people but also of the world progressives, he stressed that the followers of the Juche idea are  firmly determined to carry out his behest by devoting their all to the study and dissemination of the Juche idea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The chairman of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea expressed the determination to learn from the  experience of the DPRK in which the Juche idea has been embodied.   The President is immortal and his teachings always encourage us, he stated.

My dearest wish
