Great man's life replete with love of country
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- On the eve of the 5th death anniversary of the great leader President Kim Il Sung the Korean people look back upon his life replete with warm love of the country and the nation.   His  life, beset with difficulties and adversities and characterized by more than two decades of anti-Japanese war for national liberation and 50 year-long post-liberation responsible guidance over the country and the nation, was pervaded with his love of the country and the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In his teens he embarked upon the road of revolution to save the country and the nation. He led the hard-fought anti-Japanese revolution, eating in the wind and sleeping in the rain and dew for more than 20 years.    His love of the country and the nation is fully reflected in great many famous songs and works by him.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among those songs are  "Song of Korea," "Nostalgia," "the Flower Girl," "Song of anti-Japanese war," "Song of the ten-point program of the association for the restoration of the fatherland," and "an Autumnal Day in Mt. Myohyang."
   In his celebrated works, including "the Korean Revolutionaries Must Know Korea Well" published in September Juche 32 (1943) he underlined the time-honored history and brilliant culture of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On May 21, Juche 35 (1946) after the liberation of Korea from the Japanese colonial rule he took into his hands the first shovel to start the Pothong River improvement project for grand nature-remaking of the country. On April 6, Juche 36 (1947) he planted a tree on Mansu Hill in Pyongyang. Till the last period of his life he visited more than 18,000 units throughout the country to lay a solid groundwork for turning it into beautiful mountains and streams and bringing prosperity to the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He had warmer love of the country and the nation than anybody else. It was thanks to his wise guidance that  the ancestral father of the Korean nation with the history spanning more than 5,000 years was found and the mausoleum of the ancestral father was successfully reconstructed on an expansion basis, the history of Koguryo (277 B.C.-668) was set straight, the mausoleum of the first King Wang Kon of Koryo (877-943) was reconstructed on an expansion basis and the Songgyun-Gwan Hall of Koryo (992), Kwangbop and Jongrung temples and many other historic sites and relics are preserved carefully.

DPRK government memorandum released
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- The government of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea released a memorandum  Tuesday to hand down to all generations the undying feats  performed by the President Kim Il Sung in the history of the movement for the national reunification on the occasion of the 5th anniversary  of the historic last signature put by him to the reunification-related document in his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was hours before his death that the President read an important document on the national reunification and put the last autograph to it on July 7, Juche 83 (1994).
   It was the greatest feats the President performed in the history of the movement for the national reunification that he put forward the most realistic and aboveboard principles and methods for national reunification and showed the bright road of achieving it, the memorandum says.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the first part the memorandum points out that the President advanced the three principles of national reunification, a reunification program common to the nation, the proposal for founding the Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo, a grand plan for national reunification, and the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation, a great charter for national unity. It goes on:   On May 3, Juche 61 (1972), he received the South Korean delegate who came to Pyongyang to attend the inter-Korean high-level political talks and  made public the three principles of national reunification, which  he conceived and matured for a long time.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The three principles of national reunification -- independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity -- were recognized  by the north and the south as a common reunification program  which was followed by the publication of the historic July 4 north-south joint statement the keynote of which is the principles.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the report to the sixth congress of the  Worker's Party of Korea in October Juche 69 (1980), the President set forth an important proposal for attaining the national reunification by the method of creating a confederal state  through the concerted efforts of the north and the south with different ideas and systems  left intact.  As the only most realistic one in Korea, the proposal on creating the DCRK mirrors most fairly the interests of the north and the south.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the 5th session of the 9th Supreme People's Assembly in April Juche 82 (1993), the President reiterated the  idea of the great national unity  which calls on all the Koreans to tangibly contribute to the national reunification and the prosperity of the reunified country, those with strength dedicating their strength, those with knowledge  contributing their knowledge and those with money  donating their money,  and put forward "10-Point Program of the Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the Reunification of the Country".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the second part the memorandum says the cause of President Kim Il Sung for the national reunification has now been creditably carried forward by the great leader Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
In "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification", a historic work he published  on August 4, Juche 86 (1997) on the 52nd anniversary of the liberation of the country, he defined as the three charters of national reunification the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point program of the great unity of the whole nation and the DCRK founding proposal, advanced by the President, thus setting up a strong pillar for reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On April 18 last year, he published the historic work "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation", in which he proposed the five-point policy for great national unity -- adhering  to the principle of the national independence, uniting under the banner of patriotism and national reunification, improving the inter-Korean relations and struggling against outsiders' domination and anti-reunification forces, ensuring  travels, contacts and dialogues among all fellow countrymen and strengthening solidarity and alliance of the whole nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The five-point policy for great national unity is the great charter of national unity which evolved in depth the fatherly leader President Kim Il Sung's idea on great national unity in conformity with the requirements of new era.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, who is creditably carrying forward the respected President Kim Il Sung's instructions for national reunification, the DPRK government will do its utmost to bring earlier the independent and peaceful reunification of the country with the support and encouragement of governments and peoples  of all countries of the world loving peace and justice.

No one of south origin in north wishes to go back to S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- The South Korean authorities are now seriously abusing the human rights of the unconverted long-term prisoners by barring their repatriation to the north.   Keeping them behind bars for scores of years, they have persecuted and repressed them by every possible means.Yet, the South Korean authorities are nowadays calling for the "exchange" of the unconverted long-term prisoners for the non-existent "ROK army POWs" and "those abducted by the north" in the north.   This is a far-fetched argument to avoid the repatriation of the unconverted long-term prisoners.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Sang Jin, 42, in Hwangju county, North Hwanghae Province, said:   I was rescued by the northerners when our fishing boat was drifted away at sea in June 1992.   I would have already been dead if there had been no help from northern brothers. In the north, I have been accorded hospitality as a human being.   I settled in the north of my own accord as I found  the socialist system in the north very good. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Shamelessly enough, the South Korean authorities are describing this as an "abduction by the north".   It is preposterous for the South Korean authorities to call for the "exchange" of the unconverted long-term prisoners desirous of returning to the north for the defectors who are not willing to go back to South Korea.   There is not a single man among the defectors living in various parts of the northern half of Korea, who is willing to go back to South Korea, he stated.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Sin Kyu Thak, 71, residing in Unryul county, South Hwanghae Province, said:   The South Korean authorities'  call for "exchange" is a foolish one intended to take to the south  by force those who defected to the north of their own accord.   I served in the 17th regiment of the 8th division of the army and joined the Korean People's Army in March 1951 to fight the enemy.Defectors from "ROK army" are not "POWs".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean authorities should send back to the north all unconverted long-term prisoners who wish to come to the north, whether they are the north-origin prisoners or south-origin people.

NDFSK spokesman calls for accelerating movement for reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- The spokesman of the National Democratic Front of South Korea  (NDFSK) issued a statement on July 2 on the occasion of the 27th anniversary of the announcement of the July 4 joint statement, according to Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The spokesman said in the statement that the July 4 north-south joint statement, which embodied the three principles of national reunification -- independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity -- expounded by the great leader President Kim Il Sung, is the Juche-based program for national reunification which clarified the fundamental stand and principle of settling the issue of national reunification by the efforts of the nation in accordance with the will and interests of the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   27 years have passed since the July 4 joint statement was announced, but the nation's desire for reunification has not yet been realised, the spokesman said, and added:   The statement is faced with the critical crisis owing to the vicious moves of the "people's government."   The spokesman called upon all the people to accelerate the movement for independent reunification on the basis of the July 4 joint statement agreed upon and solemnly announced by the north and south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    The NDFSK will certainly achieve the historic cause of national reunification together with all the people who  desire independence, peace and reunification, the statement stressed.

KCNA on Cohen's remarks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- U.S. Secretary of Defense Cohen recently said that the U.S. has "war deterrent force strong enough" to provide against emergency on the Korean peninsula, according to a report.   He also said that if the DPRK test-fires a missile again, "it would complicate the four-way talks and the implementation of different agreements."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Cohen's remarks represent an impudent threat and foolish bravado of the aggressors and provocateurs, who have become extremely arrogant after the air raids on Yugoslavia as these are intended to spark a new war of aggression and justify it.
   He took issue with our self-reliant revolutionary armed forces. However, the U.S. forces are really cancer-like ones who divided the Korean peninsula and are persistently increasing the danger of war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was none other than the U.S. forces who instigated the recent armed conflict in the West Sea of Korea.   It is a sheer sophism that Cohen called the U.S. forces "deterrent force of war."  And it is impudent interference and blackmail that he pulled up us over our missile issue.   We have already repeatedly declared that such things as missile development, production and test launch belong to our sovereignty and no one has the right to take issue with the rights of a sovereign state.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A few days ago, the U.S. openly announced its test launch of an inter-continental ballistic missile. Nevertheless, the U.S. is complaining about our missile test launch. Cohen's remarks show that the U.S. warmongers are so deep in vertigo of war that they cannot distinguish the Korean peninsula  from the Balkans.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the U.S. is truly interested in the four-way talks and the implementation of the DPRK-U.S. framework agreement, it should not turn aside from the issue of replacing the armistice agreement with a peace agreement and the issue of withdrawal of its forces but, first of all, have a proper understanding of the DPRK and its self-reliant revolutionary armed forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Cohen's utterances that the U.S. is now "fully ready" betrayed his bellicose attempt to carry on the "operation plan 5027-98" at any cost and control the DPRK militarily.   We warn once again that we will punish  any provocateurs encroaching upon our national sovereignty, whoever they may be.

Opinion poll on  armed provocations in west sea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- A South Korean organization for opinion poll "right voice center" made public the results of opinion poll regarding military provocations in the West Sea of Korea  made by the present ruling quarters with the backing of the U.S., Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The organization put a written question "how do you comment on the incident in the west sea?" to 1,320 people including students, university professors, dissidents, pressmen and civilians in South Korea. 97.5 percent of  the respondents answered:    "The incident was to bridge over the ruling crisis and unleash a second Yugoslav war."   80 percent of them asserted that the backstage manipulator of the incident was the U.S.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They said that the present chief executive, who has no prerogative of the supreme command over the army, could not make such a dangerous military provocation of his own accord. The U.S. manipulated the Kim Dae Jung regime behind the incident in the west sea in a bid to spark a second Yugoslav war in the Korean peninsula.

S. Korean authorities' misuse of national songs
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 7 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries a signed commentary denouncing the South Korean rulers for their undisguised misuse of national songs.
   Popular songs created and sung under the Japanese  colonial rule are withering away or misused by others in South Korea owing to the authorities' moves to stamp out national music.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Recalling that intelligent and talented Korean writers and composers created songs representing the miserable plight of the stateless people,  resentment at Japanese imperialism and love of the country, subjected to the harsh national humiliation and suppression by the Japanese imperialists,  the commentary observes.  They bear witness to the colonial history  and ordeals and, at the same time, represent a priceless national musical legacy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The successive South Korean ruling quarters, however, indiscriminately banned songs created and disseminated in the days of the Japanese colonial rule for the mere reason that most of them were created by writers and composers who came to the north after the country's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Consequently,  many songs created by Jo Ryong Chul, Pak Yong Ho, Ri Myon Sang and Kim Hae Song, which had been so popular in the teeth of harsh suppression by the Japanese imperialists, have disappeared. This is an offspring of the South Korean authorities' hostile policy toward the north and their moves to obliterate the national culture. It is another indelible crime committed by them against the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It must not go unnoticed that songs created and sung during the period of the nation's ordeals are being undisguisedly misused. 
Nearly 1,000 songs including 500 songs written by Jo Ryong Chul have been misused by others due to swindles and frauds of the villains  who have neither ethical morality nor an iota of conscience. The missuses have been given a fabulous amount of  money for writing with the authorities' connivance.
   The South Korean authorities' moves to obliterate and misuse enlightenment songs can never be tolerated.
